
[1]maudlin

   MAUD'LIN, a. [corrupted from Magdelen, who is drawn by painters with
   eyes swelled and red with weeping.]

   Drunk; fuddled; approaching to intoxication; stupid.

   And the kind maudlin crowd melts in her praise.

                 MAUD'LIN, n. A plant of the genus Achillea.
     __________________________________________________________________

